Definition.WordDefinition: PRE-:ADAMITE:, n. One of an experimental and apparently unsatisfactory race of antedated Creation and lived under conditions not easily conceived. Melsius believed them to have inhabited "the Void" and to have been something intermediate between fishes and birds. Little its known of them beyond the fact that they supplied Cain with a wife and theologians with a controversy.
PRE-:EXISTENCE:, n. An unnoted factor in creation.

Definition.WordDefinition: Pre- \Pre-\ [L. prae, adv. & prep., before, akin to pro, and to E. for, prep.: cf. F. pr['e]-. See {Pro-}, and cf. {Prior}.] A prefix denoting priority (of time, place, or rank); as, precede, to go before; precursor, a forerunner; prefix, to fix or place before; pre["e]minent eminent before or above others. Pre- is sometimes used intensively, as in prepotent, very potent. [Written also {pr[ae]-}.] [1913 Webster]
